title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1977-03-19
lineage: Cassette transfered to DAT in the mid 90's... DAT-> Marantz CDR 615 (late 90's)-> extract wav -> Flaced with Traders little helper Level 8->Tagged. (16/44.1)
description:
Set I
Bertha, Mama Tried, Loser, Big River, They Love Each Other, Looks Like Rain, Tennessee Jed, Estimated Prophet, Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Samson & Delilah-> Playin' In The Band
Set II
Eyes Of The World-> Dancin' In The Streets-> Wharf Rat-> Franklin's Tower-> Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night, E: Uncle John's Band*
Set III

Comment
*Second Encore

reviews.review_text: Good show Wow no one reviewed this one. Very listenable audience perhaps a bit less quality than the usual bertrando & menke recordings of the era. Probably the weakest of the run but still great, killer Jerry strum-soloing in Eyes and Franklins. They are still moving Playin into interesting spots but the song won't truly blossom again till 1978
